OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAlice Sebold apologises to 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fman cleared of her rape    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, American author Alice Sebold has       
OL,6, apologised for her part in the wrongful
OL,7, conviction of a man who was cleared    
OL,8, last week of raping her in 1981.       
OL,10,FIn her memoir Lucky, she described     
OL,11,Fbeing raped and later telling police   
OL,12,Fshe had seen a black man in the street 
OL,13,Fwho she believed was her attacker.     
OL,15,FAnthony Broadwater was arrested and    
OL,16,Fconvicted, spending 16 years in prison.
OL,18,FA statement from Mr Broadwater,        
OL,19,Freleased via his lawyers, said he was  
OL,20,F"relieved that she has apologised".    
